00:38:01.130 --> 00:38:01.787
OK?

00:38:01.787 --> 00:38:02.870
Also obeys thermodynamics.

00:38:02.870 --> 00:38:03.369
Black hole.

00:38:08.277 --> 00:38:09.860
And then, you
immediately deduce there

00:38:09.860 --> 00:38:13.740
should be entropy,
because now you

00:38:13.740 --> 00:38:16.550
can just apply the first law.

00:38:16.550 --> 00:38:21.580
For example, we have the
thermodynamical relation dSdE

00:38:21.580 --> 00:38:24.220
should be 1 over t.

00:38:24.220 --> 00:38:25.180
OK?

00:38:25.180 --> 00:38:28.604
Say, if we think of
t as a function of e,

00:38:28.604 --> 00:38:30.020
then by integrating
this equation,

00:38:30.020 --> 00:38:35.190
we should deduce what is the
entropy of the black hole.

00:38:35.190 --> 00:38:40.920
So remember the t of the black
hole is 1 over-- remember,

00:38:40.920 --> 00:38:46.780
the t of the black hole,
the t of the black hole.

00:38:46.780 --> 00:38:49.550
Yeah, let me do it here.

00:38:49.550 --> 00:38:53.380
t b h of the black
hole is h bar kappa

00:38:53.380 --> 00:39:00.155
divided by 2 pi, which is the
h bar divided by 8 pi g n times

00:39:00.155 --> 00:39:00.655
m.

00:39:03.540 --> 00:39:12.380
So this would be just
8 pi g n times m h bar.

00:39:12.380 --> 00:39:14.970
Of course, you identify
the mass of the black hole

00:39:14.970 --> 00:39:20.430
with its [? image. ?]
So you identify them.

00:39:20.430 --> 00:39:23.890
So now, you can
just integrate this.

00:39:23.890 --> 00:39:27.840
You can just now become
a trivial exercise.

00:39:27.840 --> 00:39:33.870
Then you find s e
is equal to 4 pi

00:39:33.870 --> 00:39:38.470
g n e square divided by h bar.

00:39:38.470 --> 00:39:42.240
And the plus
integration constant.

00:39:42.240 --> 00:39:44.740
OK?

00:39:44.740 --> 00:39:47.140
And this integration
constant we can

00:39:47.140 --> 00:39:50.830
say to be zero, because
if the black hole have

00:39:50.830 --> 00:39:53.600
zero mass, of course
there's nothing there.

00:39:53.600 --> 00:40:00.370
And so then, we just
have this formula.

00:40:00.370 --> 00:40:03.480
So this formula can be written
a little bit more geometrically.

00:40:03.480 --> 00:40:08.330
So also remember, the black
hole-- the Schwarzschild radius

00:40:08.330 --> 00:40:11.255
is 2 g n m.

00:40:11.255 --> 00:40:13.030
OK?

00:40:13.030 --> 00:40:17.130
So this can be written a little
bit in the geometric way.

00:40:17.130 --> 00:40:24.630
So this can be written in terms
of s 4 pi r s square divided

00:40:24.630 --> 00:40:28.160
by 4 h bar g n.

00:40:28.160 --> 00:40:28.660
OK?

00:40:28.660 --> 00:40:32.410
Now g n goes to the
downstairs, because the r s

00:40:32.410 --> 00:40:34.680
contain two powers of g n.

00:40:34.680 --> 00:40:41.110
So this is given by the horizon
area of the black hole, divided

00:40:41.110 --> 00:40:44.390
by 4 h bar g n.

00:40:44.390 --> 00:40:44.890
OK?

00:40:47.510 --> 00:40:52.990
So now we conclude--
we conclude just

00:40:52.990 --> 00:40:56.660
a bit-- let's connect these
two formulas together.

00:40:56.660 --> 00:40:58.200
The temperature
of the black hole

00:40:58.200 --> 00:41:02.740
is h bar times the surface
gravity divided by 2 pi.

00:41:02.740 --> 00:41:08.580
And the entropy of a black hole
is the area of the black hole,

00:41:08.580 --> 00:41:13.700
area of the horizon of the black
hole, divided by 4 h bar g m.

00:41:13.700 --> 00:41:15.670
So as I said before,
for the black hole,

00:41:15.670 --> 00:41:19.930
there are two very important
geometric quantities.

00:41:19.930 --> 00:41:22.730
One is kappa, surface gravity.

00:41:22.730 --> 00:41:24.790
The other is the horizon area.

00:41:24.790 --> 00:41:28.970
And then they enter in a very--
in a nice and simple way,

00:41:28.970 --> 00:41:31.880
into the temperature
and the horizon--

00:41:31.880 --> 00:41:34.930
the entropy of a black hole.

00:41:34.930 --> 00:41:36.410
And let me call
this equation one.

00:41:36.410 --> 00:41:37.740
This is an important equation.

00:41:45.320 --> 00:41:49.410
So let me just note one thing.

00:41:49.410 --> 00:41:51.840
This temperature
is rather funny,

00:41:51.840 --> 00:41:56.140
